'''Chris Llewellyn''' is an American [[poet]].

==Life==
She graduated from [[Warren Wilson College]].

Her work appeared in ''Pudding House''.<ref>http://www.puddinghouse.com/pmagazine.htm</ref> 

She married Justice Department lawyer Edward Bordley.  They live in a small Northeast [[Washington, D.C.]] apartment,<ref>{{cite news| url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/washingtonpost/access/73797887.html?dids=73797887:73797887&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Feb+19%2C+1987&author=Elizabeth+Kastor&pub=The+Washington+Post+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&edition=&startpage=b.01&desc=The+Victim%27s+Verses%3B+Poet+Chris+Llewellyn+and+Her+Powerful+Fragments%27| title=The Victim's Verses; Poet Chris Llewellyn and Her Powerful Fragments'| work=The Washington Post| author=Elizabeth Kastor| date=Feb 19, 1987 }}</ref> and have a daughter, Elizabeth Bordley.<ref>http://www.takoma.com/archives/pdfs/2008/1108pdfs/takomapdfs1108/054_V1108.pdf</ref>

==Awards==
* 1986 [[List of winners of the Walt Whitman Award|Walt Whitman Award]]

